an instrument of th=\r\ne divine will, then it is neither &quot;worldly&quot; nor &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; binding nor ignor=\r\nant. The problem is not &quot;actions&quot;, but actions with &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; attachment an=\r\nd a sense of ownership, i.e. actions driven by the will and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; agend=\r\na of a limited ego.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Actions should not be spoken ill of =\r\nlike this. Detached action is a &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *sacred duty* of every being. God=\r\ns and rishis came back again and again &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; to earth to engage in deta=\r\nched action.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; If &quot;=\r\nthe atman is entirely opposed to action&quot;, then why is atman (Self) &lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; even allowing action? Why doesn&#39;t it simply halt everything? Or, is all &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; the action happening outside of atman? Is there anything outside o=\r\nf &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; atman at all?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Some buddhist philosophies coi=\r\nned the term anatman (non-Self) to &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; describe transient things. But=\r\n, in Vedic philosophy, there is no &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; anatman. All that is is atman =\r\n(Self). Ocean is permanent and still, but &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ripples that arise in i=\r\nt are transient and moving. But ripples are part &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; of ocean only an=\r\nd you do not start labeling ripples as &quot;non-ocean&quot;.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Atma=\r\nn or Purusha or Shiva is the potential energy of this cosmos, while &lt;br&gt;\n&g=\r\nt; Maya or Prakriti or Shakti is the kinetic energy of this cosmos. Shiva &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; and Shakti are seen as different entities by some people, but rish=\r\nis &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; have declared their oneness. Potential energy becomes kinetic =\r\nenergy and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; vice versa.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Atman is the still ocea=\r\nn and Maya is the force (kinetic) that gives rise &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; to moving rippl=\r\nes on the surface. A ripple that exerts itself to move in &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; a parti=\r\ncular way keeps colliding with the force and keeps moving hither &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nand tither in a chaotic way for a very long time. A ripple that does not &lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; exert itself and moves smoothly as dictated by the force will event=\r\nually &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; grind to a halt and cease to exist as a ripple on the surfa=\r\nce. It then &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; becomes part of the still ocean. If a ripple exerts i=\r\ntself to become &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; still, it may even take longer to become still. W=\r\nhat prolongs a ripple &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; is not movement but resisting the direction=\r\n given by the force and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; exerting to move in a particular way (or =\r\neven exerting to become still). &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; A ripple that surrenders to the f=\r\norce will ride the course and die down &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; faster.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n Contemplate the imagery I presented above regarding Atman and Maya, &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; ignorant/egoistic action and detached action! It is very apt.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; In not-so-distant past, sa=\r\nnnyasins remained in ashrams and isolated &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; themselves from society=\r\n and did their sadhana. Swami Vivekananda started &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; a new trend.&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; A sannyasin renounces expectation of things from people st=\r\nuck in &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; transient material world and does not depend on anyone. Bu=\r\nt he may still &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *give* basic material things to those hapless peop=\r\nle stuck in transient &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; material world! For example, Swami Vivekana=\r\nnda and his brother monks &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; went to places struck by plague, floods=\r\n, droughts, cyclones etc and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; served people. They provided food, m=\r\nedicines etc (instead of lecturing &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; that body is a transient illus=\r\nion and one should stop worrying about its &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; welfare!) and also did=\r\n construction work. They ignored the welfare of &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; their own bodies,=\r\n put themselves at risk and overcame maya personally. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; But they se=\r\nrved those still stuck in maya without looking down upon them &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; or =\r\ntheir needs or maya that trapped them! Those who wanted food got &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nfood, those who wanted medicines got medicines and those who wanted &lt;br&gt;\n&g=\r\nt; books got books. Renunciation means you do not expect anything from &lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; anyone and accept whatever comes to you naturally. It does not &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; necessarily mean rejecting or ignoring others. Overcoming maya does not=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; require belittling maya or belittling those still stuck in maya.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; The trend started by Swami Vivekananda was continued by=\r\n Swami Sivananda. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; For that reason, it is a bit weird to see him t=\r\nalking so ill of action! &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; He was obviously trying to inspire a spe=\r\ncific group of people for a &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; specific body of work. These words ar=\r\ne neither universal nor do they &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; reflect his tremendous wisdom I h=\r\nave seen elsewhere!&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&g=\r\nt; All this intellectual discussion may be satisfying to some, but the &lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; quote from Swami Brahmanananda in the other mail is very apt: &quot;You ha=\r\nve &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; been only hearing of all these spiritual things. Now realise t=\r\nhem. You &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; have done enough study and reasoning. Now do some spirit=\r\nual practice. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; First take up that aspect of God which appeals to y=\r\nou most. Follow your &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; own path of Sadhana. When you realise God th=\r\nrough it, you will feel the &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; joy of realising Him also in other as=\r\npects and through other paths.&quot;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; According to Ramakrishna=\r\n, Swami Brahmananda was a gopala who accompanied &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Lord Krishna in =\r\na previous life. His words are simple, pragmatic and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; powerful.&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; I want this forum to facilitate exchange of Vedic knowledg=\r\ne (and I will &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; also be contributing, though in spurts). But I want=\r\n more that this forum &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; should inspire people to do sadhana and fin=\r\nd God. In the end, that is &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; what matters.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Best =\r\nregards,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Narasimha&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; --------------------------------------=\r\n--------------------&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;    Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lesson=\r\ns, Jyotish Writings,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Hom=\r\nam and Pitri Tarpana:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;                    &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; targe=\r\nt=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrol=\r\noger.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;       Films that make a difference: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollo=\r\nw&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://SaraswatiFilms.org&quot;&gt;http://SaraswatiFil=\r\nms.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;       Spirituality: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blan=\r\nk&quot; href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom&quot;&gt;http://groups.yahoo.=\r\ncom/group/vedic-wisdom&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;    Jyotish writings: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow=\r\n&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings&quot;&gt;=\r\nhttp://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;                 =\r\n      Twitter ID: @homam108&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ---------------------------------